    "Name": "Beowulf",
    "Details": "The primary weapon on the Beowulf is a highly accurate large pulse laser, supported by two ER medium lasers. To make it easier for the 'Mech to hunt down its targets, the Beowulf also mounts a Beagle active probe, and a TAG target designator allows the 'Mech to designate targets for artillery attacks. To save weight on the 'Mech and still allow for high speeds, the Beowulf is powered by a 270 XL engine that weighs half as much as a standard fusion engine. It also mounts MASC, enhancing its top speed of 129.6 km/h to allow it to keep up with most light 'Mechs. To traverse rough terrain, the Beowulf has six jump jets that allow it to jump up to 180 meters. For protection from enemy fire, the Beowulf carries eight and a half tons of ferro-fibrous armor.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Extended Torso Twist</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 1.03</color></b>",
